summary: And of course, Crowley is now on consecrated ground. So he is like a man on really, really hot sand on the beach. He’s walking...
text: And of course, Crowley is now on consecrated ground. So he is like a man on really, really hot sand on the beach. He’s walking down like “Ow, ow, ow, ow”. I am writing the scene and I thought - it’s David Tennant. There is no other human being I can think of I want to do this scene.
source:
I actually decided I wanted David halfway through episode Three. And every moment after that I was writing Crowley for David. Every moment before that I was writing ‘A Crowley’. It was the scene 1941, in the Blitz, where I realized… I was writing a scene in a church. Aziraphel is in there, there are Nazi spies, he thinks he’s really clever, but he’s not. He’s in all sorts of trouble. And Crowley has to come down the aisle of the church and rescue him. 
Neil Gaiman, SXSW, March 2019 (x)

summary:
PHOTOS: David Tennant And The Cast And Creatives Of Good Omens At SXSW

  

David Tennant attended the SXSW Film Festival in...
caption:
PHOTOS: David Tennant And The Cast And Creatives Of Good Omens At SXSW

David Tennant attended the SXSW Film Festival in Austin, Texas yesterday to take part in a special Good Omens event.

Good Omens: The Nice and Accurate SXSW Event will saw showrunner and best-selling author Neil Gaiman joined by director Douglas Mackinnon, producer Rob Wilkins and cast including Michael Sheen, David Tennant, and Jon Hamm to give attendees the most in-depth look at Good Omens to date and watch never-before-seen exclusive clips from the entire series. It was part of a huge promotional event for the series centering on the Good Omens Garden of Earthly Delights, a huge immersive space of over 19000 square feet forming a hidden oasis from the impending End of Days. 

Good Omens is a dark, comedic story set in modern day Britain on the brink of the Apocalypse. When a fussy angel, Aziraphale (Michael Sheen) and a suave demon, Crowley (David Tennant) get wind of the coming of the Antichrist, they join forces to prevent the loss of their comfortable lifestyle on Earth. Throw in a medley of unforgettable characters, some infernal riders, a host of angels, a legion of demons and a gang of unruly kids, and the end of the world will never be funnier! The show also stars Michael McKean, Jack Whitehall, Adria Arjona, Mireille Enos, Nick Offerman and Nina Sosanya. It will be released worldwide on Amazon Prime on 31st May.
